 Types of files in linux:
 =======================
 
In python everything treated as object

In Linux os everything treated as File

Three types of files in Linux:
=============================
1.Normal files 
2.Directory files
3.Device Files

1.Normal files :
===============
These files contains only data i.e text files and binary files (audio,videos,images)

2.Directory files:
==================
These files represents directories

3.Device Files:
==============
Every thing in Linux treated as file  so that devices are also treated as File
Eg: USB , Terminal e.t.c


