4.tmp:
=======
tmp contains all tempory files which are related current session

5.dev:
=====
dev means device
all device files will be stored inside dev directory

6.mnt:
======
mnt means mounting

The files which are in external devices lik pen drive,cd ....attached to linux file system
This process is known as mounting 
1.maual mounting
2.automatic mounting

5.media:
=======
The files of automatic mounting will be placed inside media directory

8.opt:
======
opt means optional

it contains third party softwares 

9.lib:
=======
lib means library

It contains all library files related to our commands

10.var:
=======
var means variable
 The files which are keep on changes those files stored var directory
 Eg: logfile
 
11.home:
=======
Linux os multople user os 
Every user having their own home directory
12 .Proc:
========
Proc means process directory
Linux os is multi tasking system
At a time multiple tasks will running 
Each task having their own Process ID (PID)
PID information will be stored in proc directory
13 .root:
=========

root is directory which act as home directory for admin user

14.usr:
======
usr means user
all user realted softwares

15. boot:
============
boot contains files which are related to boot linux os



